Hypothesis testing¶

In [45]:
#hypothesis testiong is a statistical procedure used to draw conclusions on a dataset.
#hypothesis s nothing but assumptions.and to find that whether our assumptions are mathcing or not.
#let Null hypothesis be: H0 -- where variables A(SepalLengthCm 	SepalWidthCm 	PetalLengthCm 	PetalWidthCm) are independent to varaible B(Species)
#Alternate hypothesis be:H1 -- where variables A(SepalLengthCm 	SepalWidthCm 	PetalLengthCm 	PetalWidthCm) are not independent to varaible B(Species)
#lets perform CHI_SQUARE TEST on the dataset to conclude the hypothesis.
In [46]:
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency
from scipy.stats import chi2


chi, p_value, dof, expected=chi2_contingency(pd.crosstab(df['Species'], df['PetalWidthCm']))
print("chi_squared_stat :", chi)
probability=0.95
critical=chi2.ppf(probability, dof)
if abs(chi)>=critical:
    print('Dependent')
elif abs(chi)<critical:
    print('Inependent')

chi_squared_stat : 271.75
Dependent
